You can download releases from there as well.</p>
<h2 id="global-keybindings">Global keybindings</h2>
<ul>
<li>CTRL+ALT+a - quick add a task</li>
<li>CTRL+ALT+t - show or hide the app window</li>
</ul>
<p>These are the only keybindings I need. If you need anything else let me know.</p>
<h2 id="motivation">Motivation</h2>
<p>I thought it should be good idea to have Todoist opened as an application instead of tab in a browser.</p>
<p>Todoist supports a lot of different platforms but not Linux.
So I&rsquo;ve made Electron wrapper for Todoist&rsquo;s web version.</p>
<p>The main reason why I couldn&rsquo;t use it as a web version is lack of global keybindings.</p>
<p>Let me know about bugs or features you want to see in the project.</p>